        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This example shows how to specify a custom position for a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph> control when the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.Placement%2A&gt;</ph> property is set to <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.PlacementMode&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.Placement%2A&gt;</ph> property is set to <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.PlacementMode&gt;</ph>, the <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph> calls a defined instance of the <ph id="ph4">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.CustomPopupPlacementCallback&gt;</ph> delegate.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This delegate returns a set of possible points that are relative to the top left corner of the target area and the top left corner of the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph> placement occurs at the point that provides the best visibility.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following example shows how to define the position of a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph> by setting the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.Placement%2A&gt;</ph> property to <ph id="ph3">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.PlacementMode&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It also shows how to create and assign a <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.CustomPopupPlacementCallback&gt;</ph> delegate in order to position the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The callback delegate returns two <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.CustomPopupPlacement&gt;</ph> objects.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph> is hidden by a screen edge at the first position, the <ph id="ph2">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup&gt;</ph> is placed at the second position.</source>
        </trans-unit>
